#: course/lesson-20-looping-over-arrays/lesson.bbcode:106
msgctxt "practice.1.hint"
msgid "In the loop, you first need to call [code]draw_rectangle()[/code], and then [code]jump()[/code]. Otherwise, at least two rectangles will overlap."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-20-looping-over-arrays/lesson.bbcode:106
msgctxt "practice.1.hint"
msgid "The arguments when calling [code]jump()[/code] can just be large enough to space out the rectangles. For example, [code]jump(300, 0)[/code]"
